A woman died and four people were injured when the car they were travelling in rolled on the N12 about 10km from Ogies heading towards Witbank in Mpumalanga on Sunday. An off-duty paramedic came across the incident and called for further resources, ER24 spokeswoman Chitra Bodasing-Harduth said. The car was found lying on it side in the veld. Upon assessment of one woman found lying near the vehicle it was found that she had sadly died. Another woman found lying close to the vehicle was assessed and treated for moderate injuries. Three other patients were treated for minor injuries. Patients were transported to hospital for further medical care, she said. The cause of the accident was unknown.